The paper deals with the classification of malware using deep learning techniques, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of deep learning for feature extraction and selection also suggests the possibility of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) being a relevant sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of Support Vector Machine (SVM) as a classifier, which is a popular machine learning algorithm and falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the importance of reducing the chances of missing a malware, which suggests the possibility of software engineering (cs.SE) being a relevant sub-category. Finally, the use of Multilayer Perceptron (MLP) as a classifier suggests the possibility of neural networks (cs.NE) being a relevant sub-category.
